    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-12-18T14:09:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-12-18T14:09:00-05:00" n="252"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                <head>252. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">United
                        Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d252fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 737.56361/12-1862. Top Secret. Drafted and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName> and cleared in substance
                        with the President.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-12-18T14:09:00-05:00">December 18, 1962, 2:09 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1687. Eyes only for <persName corresp="#p_SAEII1">Stevenson</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_MCJJ1">McCloy</persName>. At a suitable occasion in
                    our negotiations with <persName corresp="#p_KVV2">Kuznetsov</persName> and in
                    connection with any discussion with him on the question of our continued
                    reconnaissance, you should express to <persName corresp="#p_KVV2"
                        >Kuznetsov</persName> our growing concern over fact Soviets are continuing
                    work at and improve anti-aircraft arsenal in Cuba. We are concerned that someone
                    might have the motive of interfering with our reconnaissance. We have made it
                    amply clear to the Soviets that, in the absence of other safeguards, we must and
                    will continue that reconnaissance. We have no desire to return to the days of
                    late October and assume this is also shared by the Soviets. The Soviets must
                    recognize that destruction of American aircraft and loss of American life
                    arising from this deliberate activity of the Soviet Union could well have such
                    consequences. We hope <persName corresp="#p_KVV2">Kuznetsov</persName> will
                    understand that our motive in bringing this to his attention is simply to make
                    sure that there is no misunderstanding on this point. In short, we feel it would
                    be unwise continue this buildup in view of the non-belligerent and
                    non-provocative character and intent of our reconnaissance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD3">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
